<div id="review_3946805900" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3946805900" />
    <a title="Elysse" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/72401291-elysse"><img alt="Elysse" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1604672195p2/72401291.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3946805900?book_show_action=true">Apr 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elysse" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elysse" href="/user/show/72401291-elysse">Elysse</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3946805900" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11997875142817840408">As a total historical nerd and affirmed addict to period fiction, I was totally sucked into the world of Lost Love&apos;s Return! Set in America around the events of the first World War, Alfred Nicols has written a relentlessly captivating drama. The book does such a great job of describing just how different (though, in many ways similar) the world of early 20th century America was, and the gut-wrenching decisions people were forced to make as part of everyday life. The book follows protagonist Pete</span>
  <span id="freeText11997875142817840408" style="display:none">As a total historical nerd and affirmed addict to period fiction, I was totally sucked into the world of Lost Love's Return! Set in America around the events of the first World War, Alfred Nicols has written a relentlessly captivating drama. The book does such a great job of describing just how different (though, in many ways similar) the world of early 20th century America was, and the gut-wrenching decisions people were forced to make as part of everyday life. The book follows protagonist Peter Montgomery, whose life is cleaved in two by his conscription to the “Great War.” As he embarks on his military journey, his life becomes fractured between a lost past and relentless future, as well as between two love interests that become the source of a heart-breaking romance. Ultimately, the story hinges on Peter’s efforts to seek out and reclaim his lost love over multiple continents over the course of nearly 50 years. <br /><br />Totally compelling. Lost Love's Return will more than satisfy any fans of romance or historical fiction. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11997875142817840408" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


