<div id="review_3952269986" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3952269986" />
    <a title="Kym Jones" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/77524923-kym-jones"><img alt="Kym Jones" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1518117845p2/77524923.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3952269986?book_show_action=true">Apr 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kym Jones" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kym Jones" href="/user/show/77524923-kym-jones">Kym Jones</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3952269986" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12792222829173741347">Lost Love&apos;s Return is a poignant love story that literally hits the reader in the heart and takes the reader on the journey of a lifetime, living through the joys and sorrows of Alfred Nicols characters that seem to draw you into their lives whether you realize it or not.<br/><br/>I must admit I am not usually a fan of stories where the lead characters are separated for years like they are in Lost Love&apos;s Return, but after reading the synopsis, I just had to give this book a chance, I am so very glad I did</span>
  <span id="freeText12792222829173741347" style="display:none">Lost Love's Return is a poignant love story that literally hits the reader in the heart and takes the reader on the journey of a lifetime, living through the joys and sorrows of Alfred Nicols characters that seem to draw you into their lives whether you realize it or not.<br /><br />I must admit I am not usually a fan of stories where the lead characters are separated for years like they are in Lost Love's Return, but after reading the synopsis, I just had to give this book a chance, I am so very glad I did! <br /><br />This book is one where you feel like you are living in the actual pages of the book, and Peter and Elizabeth quickly become family to you instead of just characters on paper pages - or electronic pages as the case may be. You get angry at many of the choices Peter makes, and some that Elizabeth does, because you know they belong together but there is really nothing they can do at the time (at least some of the time) but you still have to keep reading just to find out if they find their happily ever after. <br /><br />For people that love Nicholas Sparks, they will love Alfred Nicols debut novel, Lost Love Return. This is a must-read for anyone that loves a classic style romance.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12792222829173741347" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


