<div id="review_3895055565" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3895055565" />
    <a title="Marissa DeCuir" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2967349-marissa-decuir"><img alt="Marissa DeCuir" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1450288802p2/2967349.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3895055565?book_show_action=true">Mar 17, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marissa DeCuir" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marissa DeCuir" href="/user/show/2967349-marissa-decuir">Marissa DeCuir</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3895055565" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5836892797539431373">As a person who grew up in the small town south, I really loved the way this book illustrated Peter Montgomery&apos;s struggles. Thankfully, I never had to serve in war or live through the great depression! But I loved reading Lost Love&apos;s Return because I thought Peter’s story was so relatable in so many ways. The writing itself was also impressive and the plot was really well-paced. I ended up reading this book in two sittings! If you see this book and you’re from the south, or if you’re just a hope</span>
  <span id="freeText5836892797539431373" style="display:none">As a person who grew up in the small town south, I really loved the way this book illustrated Peter Montgomery's struggles. Thankfully, I never had to serve in war or live through the great depression! But I loved reading Lost Love's Return because I thought Peter’s story was so relatable in so many ways. The writing itself was also impressive and the plot was really well-paced. I ended up reading this book in two sittings! If you see this book and you’re from the south, or if you’re just a hopeless romantic, I heartily recommend it!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5836892797539431373" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


