<div id="review_3948236715" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3948236715" />
    <a title="Angelle Barbazon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43008764-angelle-barbazon"><img alt="Angelle Barbazon" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3948236715?book_show_action=true">Apr 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Angelle Barbazon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Angelle Barbazon" href="/user/show/43008764-angelle-barbazon">Angelle Barbazon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3948236715" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8252019654986626731">I was surprised by how much I enjoyed this book. I have not done a lot of fiction reading recently but once I began reading Lost Love&apos;s Return, I could not put it down. I’m not usually interested in history or historical fiction but this book sucked me right in. I was especially moved by the main character’s relationships and how different things were in America before people had things like the internet and TV to keep them occupied. I don’t usually like romance books that much but the drama of </span>
  <span id="freeText8252019654986626731" style="display:none">I was surprised by how much I enjoyed this book. I have not done a lot of fiction reading recently but once I began reading Lost Love's Return, I could not put it down. I’m not usually interested in history or historical fiction but this book sucked me right in. I was especially moved by the main character’s relationships and how different things were in America before people had things like the internet and TV to keep them occupied. I don’t usually like romance books that much but the drama of Peter lost love and the tension of his dysfunctional marriage got me hooked. Despite all the turmoil and drama, the book was a great break from the stress and real-world drama of the past year. This book kept me going and left me happy. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8252019654986626731" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


