<div id="review_3895031992" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3895031992" />
    <a title="Books Forward" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40613272-books-forward"><img alt="Books Forward" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1590523809p2/40613272.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3895031992?book_show_action=true">Mar 17, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Books Forward" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Books Forward" href="/user/show/40613272-books-forward">Books Forward</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3895031992" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2358894456223694274">For anyone who has a place in their heart for a hopeless romantic in their life, a love of history, or has ever experienced heartbreak, we can confidently say you will love Lost Love&apos;s Return. The story follows the seemingly doomed romance of a heartbroken young man from a small town in Mississippi who enlists WW1 and falls in love with a military nurse who helps repair his injured leg. When the two are ultimately separated by the war the novel follows his struggle to lead a happy life in her ab</span>
  <span id="freeText2358894456223694274" style="display:none">For anyone who has a place in their heart for a hopeless romantic in their life, a love of history, or has ever experienced heartbreak, we can confidently say you will love Lost Love's Return. The story follows the seemingly doomed romance of a heartbroken young man from a small town in Mississippi who enlists WW1 and falls in love with a military nurse who helps repair his injured leg. When the two are ultimately separated by the war the novel follows his struggle to lead a happy life in her absence and his long, long journey to eventually reconnect with his true love after falling being manipulated into a toxic relationship after the war. This book was very well written and engrossing. It also takes place along the eventful historical timeline of the years between the years of WW1 through the end of WW2. The author, Alfred Nicols, has described this book as a labor of love and, after reading Lost Love's Return, it’s clear his work paid off.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2358894456223694274" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


