<div id="review_4054116671" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4054116671" />
    <a title="Beverly Kraft" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/136329569-beverly-kraft"><img alt="Beverly Kraft" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4054116671?book_show_action=true">Jun 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Beverly Kraft" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Beverly Kraft" href="/user/show/136329569-beverly-kraft">Beverly Kraft</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4054116671" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9662327445253745199"> Author Alfred Nicols had a successful career as an attorney, a state trial judge and a federal magistrate judge. He painted late into the evenings, and sometimes all night, attaining a reputation as a talented and sought-after Southern landscape artist. After he retired from the bench, Nicols painted full-time. An artist for more than 50 years, Nicols devoted painstaking attention to detail in ever stroke of his brush. He has applied that same attention to detail in his first published novel, c</span>
  <span id="freeText9662327445253745199" style="display:none"> Author Alfred Nicols had a successful career as an attorney, a state trial judge and a federal magistrate judge. He painted late into the evenings, and sometimes all night, attaining a reputation as a talented and sought-after Southern landscape artist. After he retired from the bench, Nicols painted full-time. An artist for more than 50 years, Nicols devoted painstaking attention to detail in ever stroke of his brush. He has applied that same attention to detail in his first published novel, creating a love story set against the horrors of war. He tells a story of love, loss, longing and redemption. The plot at its core explores the choices we make in life, and their consequences.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9662327445253745199" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


